metadata.description: MLI = 100 represents the purchasing power of the average US household in 2019 (pre-pandemic baseline)
metadata.formula: MLI = (Median Income / Total Cost of Living) / 5.2755 × 100
metadata.col_interpretation: Cost of Living represents total estimated annual expenses for a median household
changes_from_v1: COL is now total annual expenses (not weighted basket)
MLI uses fixed 2019 baseline (not yearly floating average)
